observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management agreed to enhance its mechanisms on accounting and property custodianship of its PPE through the following:
a. Conduct a complete and thorough physical inventory-taking and consequently, a reconciliation of accounts. Determine whether remaining unrecognized assets which were found at the station are owned by the Municipality. Once identified under the Municipality, appraised such assets and recognized on proper accounts. For items identified as for reclassification, revisit standards and related issuances on these items for proper account to be used;
b. Enhance accountabilities over assets through identifying and updating records and monitoring particularly on Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment which should be renewed every three (3) years;
c. Commence depreciation of immovable properties once it is already in use. Determine unrecognized prior years and current year depreciation of these assets and reflect in the statement of changes in equity and statement of financial performance, respectively;
d. Identify all equipment which are primarily used for response and rescue operations as well as their corresponding costs and accumulated depreciations then reclassify said equipment to Disaster Response and Rescue Equipment account. Revisit guidelines provided under COA Circular 2012-002 for proper accounting and reporting of these equipment and other related items included therein;
e. Identify uninsured assets and prioritize the processing of assets with more exposure on risk of deterioration or damage due to fortuitous event. Consider, the significance of possible loss which may occur due to any unexpected and unforeseen events; and
f. Establish a General Services Office as a separate unit with personnel focusing on the main duties and responsibilities of the office as provided by the Local Government Code of the Philippines.

