We recommended that management :
1. prepare an adjusting entry/ies to recognize the advances granted to various LSB members by debiting and crediting the account Advances to Officers and Employees and Government Equity, respectively;
2. enforce compliance with the afore-cited rules and regulations and stop the improper/irregular practice of recording advances as outright expenses;
3. immediately submit the Report of Disbursement to COA for further audit; and
4. require the accountant to set up the corresponding subsidiary ledgers of financial assistance for easy monitoring of the liquidation.
